ina and the results rozelle says are shocking children who received the multivitamin with iron had lower anemia rates and scored higher on tests than children in two control groups the stanford report campaign supports researchers as they develop real world solutions to vexing problems search fsi search within everything courses events fellowships news op eds people publications research other pages news of interest researchers explore potential solutions to mexican crime and violence november 22 2011 cisac fsi stanford cddrl program on poverty and governance announcement ips students tackling real world policy problems june 1 2011 cddrl fsi stanford fsi stanford fsi stanford fsi stanford fsi stanford news join us at our climate policy instruments in the real world conference june 22 2010 pesd news bill gates finding a way to make a difference in the news stanford report on april 20 2010 problems of membership seeking solutions to expansion integration and intervention in globalized europe august 1 2007 fsi stanford the europe center news chemist applies her science and entrepreneurial know how to solve real world security problems cisac in the news chemical and engineering news on december 13 2004 support map & directions contact rss+ rss xml feeds freeman spogli institute for international studies encina hall 616 serra st stanford ca 94305 6055 tel 650 723 4581 fax 650 725 2592 mail code 6055
